    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI use 'smartcase' and `completeopt+=longest` so I can type lowercase and complete into the correct case. After upgrading to nvim 0.12, this feature no longer works correctly. If completing \"inp\" can match \"Inp\", then that's filled in which due to 'smartcase' prevents matches that start with \"INP\" or \"inp\". Since I never input uppercase, the partial completion should maintain my input case until I select a match.\n\n'infercase' is not a viable solution because I'm writing code and need the final match to be the correct case.\n\nI first noticed this incorrect behaviour on NVIM v0.12.2.\n\n## Workaround\n\nUsing either of these settings prevents the bug:\n`nosmartcase`\n`completeopt-=longest `\n\nBut it means giving up those very useful features.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -u c:/scratch/vimtest.lua  c:/scratch/vimtest.gd\n\nc:/scratch/vimtest.lua:\n```lua\nvim.opt.completeopt:append \"longest\"\nvim.o.ignorecase = true\nvim.o.smartcase = true\n```\n\nc:/scratch/vimtest.gd\n```gdscript\nfunc _input(event: InputEvent):\n        var inputmap = PlayerInputDef.INPUT_MAP\n```\n\n(gdscript doesn't matter, can be .txt and problem still occurs.)\n\nType `inp<C-n>`.\n\nThe only completion offered is `InputEvent`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExpected all smartcase matches:\n`InputEvent`\n`inputmap`\n`INPUT_MAP`\n\nThis is the behaviour on NVIM v0.11.5.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-713+g2e8c60cb38\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, VIM MS-Windows 64-bit GUI - 9.0.1576\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWin11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ncmd.exe and neovide\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nnone (Windows)\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-17T01:16:32Z",
