    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This fixes the problem with a lower-case pattern:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/insexpand.c b/src/nvim/insexpand.c\nindex 546f618a30..b632bb556f 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/insexpand.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/insexpand.c\n@@ -1582,8 +1582,8 @@ static int ins_compl_build_pum(void)\n     String *leader = get_leader_for_startcol(comp, true);\n \n     // Apply 'smartcase' behavior during normal mode\n-    if (ctrl_x_mode_normal() && !p_inf && leader->data\n-        && !ignorecase(leader->data) && !cot_fuzzy()) {\n+    if (ctrl_x_mode_normal() && !p_inf && compl_pattern.data\n+        && !ignorecase(compl_pattern.data) && !cot_fuzzy()) {\n       comp->cp_flags &= ~CP_ICASE;\n     }\n \n@@ -5058,7 +5058,7 @@ static char *find_common_prefix(size_t *prefix_len, bool curbuf_only)\n     String *leader = get_leader_for_startcol(compl, true);\n \n     // Apply 'smartcase' behavior during normal mode\n-    if (ctrl_x_mode_normal() && !p_inf && leader->data && !ignorecase(leader->data)) {\n+    if (ctrl_x_mode_normal() && !p_inf && compl_pattern.data && !ignorecase(compl_pattern.data)) {\n       compl->cp_flags &= ~CP_ICASE;\n     }\n \n```\n\nHowever an upper-case pattern still doesn't work properly with 'smartcase' and \"longest\": `I<C-N>` only completes `InputEvent` while `I<C-P>` only completes `INPUT_MAP`.",
